README.md
     5â†’## Usage
     7â†’To start using the library, install it in your project:
     8â†’
     9â†’```bash
    10â†’npm install sonner
    11â†’```
    12â†’
    13â†’Add `<Toaster />` to your app, it will be the place where all your toasts will be rendered.
    14â†’After that you can use `toast()` from anywhere in your app.
    15â†’
    16â†’```jsx
    17â†’import { Toaster, toast } from 'sonner';
    18â†’
    19â†’// ...
    20â†’
    21â†’function App() {
    22â†’  return (
    23â†’    <div>
    24â†’      <Toaster />
    25â†’      <button onClick={() => toast('My first toast')}>Give me a toast</button>
    26â†’    </div>
    27â†’  );
    28â†’}
    29â†’```
    30â†’
    31â†’## Documentation
    33â†’Find the full API reference in the [documentation](https://sonner.emilkowal.ski/getting-started).
